<item>
            <title>[AVRO-1799] java: GenericData.toString() mutates underlying ByteBuffer backed data</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1799</link>
                <project id="12310911" key="AVRO">Apache Avro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Around line 550, the writeEscapedString() method, used to serialize a byte array, will alter the underlying ByteBuffer&apos;s pointer.  Meaning subsequent uses of a toString()&apos;d avro object will yield different results.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Need to not use a generic decode on a ByteBuffer; either clone the element (expensive), or iterate over the elements with an external index.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12938217">AVRO-1799</key>
            <summary>java: GenericData.toString() mutates underlying ByteBuffer backed data</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="2" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/critical.svg">Critical</priority>
                        <status id="5" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/resolved.png" description="A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.">Resolved</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
